Diagrams and Schematics:

Submitted the Fifth Round PCBway Orders by 4:45 PM after passing the audit, incorporating all necessary design modifications based on previous testing feedback.
Design Problems and Decisions:

Servo Motor Overload: Identified that some servo motors were unable to handle the increased torque demands due to extended arm lengths. Decided to upgrade to higher-torque servo motors to meet performance requirements.
Power Distribution: Implemented an additional power supply channel dedicated to the upgraded servo motors to prevent overloading existing voltage regulators.
