Important Notes for Debugging:

Ensure that the upgraded servo motors are correctly integrated into the power subsystem to prevent voltage drops and maintain torque performance.
Verify that all demonstration materials accurately represent the system's capabilities and are free from technical inaccuracies.
Analysis and Proposed Solutions for Debugging Problems:

Detected that the upgraded servo motors were drawing more current than anticipated, causing voltage regulators to strain. Proposed adding a dedicated voltage regulator channel with higher current capacity to support the additional load.
Noted potential issues with servo motor overheating under extended operation and planned to implement additional cooling measures.
Documentation of New Tests:

Scheduled to perform comprehensive power distribution tests to ensure that the dedicated voltage regulator channel can handle the additional load without compromising system stability.
Planned to conduct extended servo motor operation tests to verify torque performance and thermal stability.
Documentation of Final Performance Tests and Design Verification:

Scheduled full system integration tests once the Fifth Round PCBs are received and assembled, ensuring that all subsystems operate harmoniously and meet design specifications.
